<h1>
	ScoutTrax User Guide
</h1>

<h2>
	Welcome
</h2>

<p>
	Welcome to <a id="scouttraxlink" href="www.scouttrax.org">ScoutTrax.org</a>, an innovative scout tracking tool with
	features you won't find together in any other scout tracking software.
	ScoutTrax was created by software professionals who do this for free
	because they are passionate about scouting.
</p>

<p>
	<h3>
		ScoutTrax is:
	</h3>
</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		<h4>
			Simple and free, one-click tracking.
		</h4>
	</li>
	<ul>
		<li>
			View a scout's complete record on a single page.
		</li>
		<li>
			Don't worry about whether the next scout master or sponsoring
			organization will continue to pay for the program. It is free and
			will stay free.
		</li>

		<li>
			Smart software: i.e. if your leader registers in a particular city,
			ScoutTrax assumes everyone else will be in the same city. You don't
			spend time putting in the same city, state and zip code for every
			single user.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<li>
		<h4>
			Accessible to scouts, parents and leaders on the web, all the time.
		</h4>
	</li>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Gives the power to the scout to be more involved with his own progress.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<li>
		<h4>
			Facilitates communication between scouts, parents and leaders.
		</h4>
	</li>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Automatically emails reminders and status updates to all.
		</li>

		<li>
			scouts, leaders, and parents all have access to their records and
			provide a check and balance for entered data.
		</li>
		<li>
			ScoutTrax keeps track of information not kept by the council's
			program. For example, a scout's leadership position history, camping
			history, service hours, and partial merit badges are tracked and
			easily communicated to a succeeding scout master.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<li>
		<h4>
			Safe, Secure and Private
		</h4>
	</li>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Data is kept safe by regular offsite data backups.
		</li>
		<li>
			Privacy is protected by encrypted passwords and other security
			measures.
		</li>

	</ul>
	<h2>
		Getting Started
	</h2>

	<p style="color:red;font-size:1.3em;">
		Watch the "Getting Started" video on the home page. It will step you
		through the following:
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li>
			Create a ScoutTrax account
		</li>
		<ol>
			<li>
				Download the PDF or ASPX of your scout's advancement records from
				your council website. This link is usually found on your council
				website. Scoutmasters and unit leaders will know the unit ID
				required for this step.
			</li>
			<li>
				Login to your advancement link from your council's website. (Only
				Internet Explorer and Firefox will work. Chrome and Safari will not
				work.)
			</li>
			<li>
				Click on "Unit Advancement Summary" in the upper right corner.
			</li>
			<li>
				Once the file loads, save it. By default it will have the name of
				"UnitAdvancementSummary.aspx" If you will be downlowding more than
				one unit record, you may want to rename it, i.e.
				TroopAdvancementSumary.aspx, or TeamAdvancementSumary.aspx, or
				CrewAdvancementSumary.aspx.
			</li>
			<li>
				Then login to ScoutTrax.org.
			</li>
			<li>
				On the troop management page, next to the "Select Unit Advancement
				PDF file" select the "Browse...".
			</li>
			<li>
				Select the the file you downloaded above.
			</li>
			<li>
				Select import. After a few minutes you should see your scouts' names
				appear on the right side with all the council records now imported.
			</li>
			<li>
				Repeat this process if necessary for other units (i.e. Troop, Team
				or Crew).
			</li>
		</ol>
	</ul>

