	<h2>
		Features
	</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Automatic emails</b> are sent to the scout when a leader makes
			changes to his merit badges, campouts, service or other items.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Scout birthday reminders</b> are automatically e-mailed to the
			scout's leaders. Some items such as the Eagle award are affected by a
			birthday. The leaders are emailed 30 days before the scout's birthday
			and again the day of the scout's birthday. This will help the leader
			remember to review that scout's record to make sure he is ready to
			progress. It also gives the new leader advanced notice so he can
			prepare for the incoming scout.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Security</b> is ensured with password encrypted and protected
			accounts.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Reports</b> can be customized by date. This makes it easier to
			report changes since the last Court of Honor or to see how a scout
			has been progressing over a given time period.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Personalize</b> a scout's account by uploading his photo.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Provide feedback</b> in the top right corner next to the Logout
			link. Your feedback will be used to address individual concerns and
			to know what features to add next.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Record Transfer-</b> Scouts can be transferred to another troop.
			If the scout's new troop is not using ScoutTrax, the new troop is
			given the opportunity to create an account in ScoutTrax. They can
			begin to use ScoutTrax or simply retrieve the scout's information.
		</li>
		<li>
			Looks and performs like your scout book, but you will never lose it.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Easy</b> to learn and to use for one scout or 100.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Password recovery</b> is available when a scout or leader has
			forgotten it. The password is sent to the e-mail that ScoutTrax has
			on record for that user.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Backups- </b> All data is backed up regularly off-site to prevent
			data loss, and to allow quick recovery.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<ul>
		<li>
			<b>Merit Badge Tracking-</b> Tracks merit badges earned and which
			requirements of partially completed merit badges have been completed.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Service Tracking-</b> Tracks service hours for each scout.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Camp Tracking-</b> Tracks camping history of each scout. This
			feature is very useful for verifying requirements for the camping
			merit badge.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Leadership</b>
			<b>Tracking-</b> Tracks a scout's leadership history.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Duty to God tracking-</b> The "DTG" tab is for tracking the scout's
			progress in the requirements of the Church of Jesus Christ of
			Latter-Day Saints. This is not meant to replace the church's own
			website, which is an excellent resource, but allows a leader to see
			where all the scouts are at once. Also, it provides one place and one
			way to keep track of a scout's progress in scouting and/or with Duty To
			God.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Enter data for several scouts at once.</b> Choose any number of
			scouts when passing off requirements for merit badges or adding data
			such as camping information. This reduces time when recording the
			same data for more than one scout. Leaders can even do this with a
			single click.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>At-a-glance information for a selected scout.</b> When a scout is
			selected, the images of his earned merit badges display at the top of
			the page. The rank the scout is working on along with any partial
			merit badge are displayed in the right pane.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Not just a scout master's tool-</b> Each scout or parent can have
			a personalized account. This allows a scout or parent to see and
			update his progress at any time. For privacy reasons, they cannot
			view other scouts' records, like a leader can.
		</li>
		<li>
			<b>Like a scout book,</b> each parent or scout can sign off awards
			and requirements. However, only leaders can sign off things like a
			Scout Master Conference or a Board of Review. FYI: When a leader
			views the records, requirements Recorded by a parent or scout will be
			outlined in red. He may choose to focus more heavily on these
			requirements at the Scout Master Conference.
		</li>
		<li>
			If there is a popular new feature people want, we'll add it. Just
			click on the
			<b>feedback</b> link in the upper right hand corner of the software,
			or comment on
			<b>facebook.com/ScoutTrax</b> to report problems, ask questions or
			give suggestions.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>
		Hints and Tips
	</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>
			First select the scout(s) whose record(s) you would like to update.
			Then pass off the requirement or award with just one click.
		</li>
		<li>
			Leaders may add or change the image of a scout or update other
			information, by selecting the scout from the list on the right. Then
			click on the box at the bottom with the scout's personal information.
		</li>
		<li>
			Click on the image of the scout to get an instant view of his
			accomplishments.
		</li>
		<li>
			Click on the the troop's unit number to view personal information, or
			for leaders, this will allow you to manage your troop membership,
			troop records, and send invitations.
		</li>
		<li>
			Click on the scout's information at the bottom of the scout book page
			to go to the main window where you can see and modify his
			information.
		</li>
		<li>
			Entering a scout's birthday will activate the birthday reminder
			feature which automatically sends an email to remind the leader when
			a birthday is approaching.
		</li>
		<li>
			Leaders can put a check mark in the box next to multiple scouts then
			enter the data. This will enter the data for all selected scouts.
		</li>
		<li>
			Add a scout or a leader by clicking the "troop number" image. Click
			on the appropriate button and fill in the person's name and related
			information.
		</li>
		<li>
			Leaders can invite a scout to access this program by clicking on the
			check box next to his name; then click "Send Invitation." This will
			e-mail an invitation to each selected person.
		</li>
		<li>
			When leaders review an individual scout's record, the requirements
			passed off by someone other than the leader, are outlined in red.
			This assists in the Scout Master Conference and Board of Review, to
			help the leader to know what to verify.
		</li>
	</ul>